The cabinet shall prepare an annual report on the program to be submitted to the Governor and the Legislative Research Commission and made available to the public for review during the cabinet's normal business hours. The report shall include:
The number and location of courses offered;
The number of instructors approved;
The number of students trained in various courses;
The number of permits, licenses, and registrations issued;
The amount of money collected by category for permits, licenses, and registrations;
Other information about program implementation as the cabinet shall deem appropriate; and
An assessment of the overall impact of the program on motorcycle safety in the state. The report shall also provide a complete accounting of revenue receipts of the motorcycle safety education program fund and of all moneys expended under the program.
